Task Object Constructor: The Task class defines the structure of a task with id, description, and priority properties.
TaskManager Class: The TaskManager class handles task management operations:
addTask(description, priority): Adds a new task.
viewTasks(): Returns all tasks.
updateTask(id, newDescription, newPriority): Updates a task's description and priority.
deleteTask(id): Deletes a task by ID.
fetchTaskInfo(taskId): Simulates fetching additional information for a task from an external API using async/await.
Example Usage: Demonstrates adding, updating, deleting tasks, and fetching additional information using the TaskManager class.
